data: {"type":"layer1","modelId":"local/apple-fm","model":"Crucible (offline)","text":"## Revised Zod Schema for IPv4 Address Validation\n\n```json\n{\n  \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\",\n  \"title\": \"IPv4 Address\",\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"ip\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"pattern\": \"^(25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9]{2}){3}$\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"required\": [\"ip\"]\n}\n```\n\n## Explanation\n\n- **$schema**: Specifies the JSON Schema version.\n- **title**: The title of the schema.\n- **type**: The type of the schema, which is an object.\n- **properties**: A key-value pair where each key is a property name and the value is the schema for that property.\n  - **ip**: A string representing the IPv4 address.\n    - **type**: String.\n    - **pattern**: A regular expression that matches a valid IPv4 address. It ensures the address has exactly four octets, each ranging from 0 to 255.\n- **required**: An array of property names that are required for the schema to be valid.\n\nThis schema validates an IPv4 address by checking that it consists of exactly four octets, each ranging from 0 to 255.","done":true}

